        <abstract> 
<p>Appreciates MJB’s address [<hi rend="italic">Rep. BAAS</hi> 38 (1868): 83–7]. Has had great respect for MJB’s knowledge since his undergraduate days at Cambridge.</p> 
            <p>Agrees that Pangenesis gemmules probably do not develop into free cells, but penetrate other cells in a manner analogous to fertilisation, and modify their development.</p>
        </abstract>
